title: What’s News: World-Wide
text:
The U.S. administration’s tit-for-tat with Beijing over potential tariffs has ushered in a high-stakes standoff over trade. The two sides will now follow a timeline stretching over the next half year, during which they will seek to negotiate a new normal.
Trump has agreed to keep U.S. troops in Syria but only until Islamic State is defeated, a task he expects to be finished in months.
